ps:0  A bright red, green and yellow arch
rises over the entrance to the Eden Center marketplace.
Lion statues sit to the right and left, as
if on guard. Smells of sweet and spicy food
flow out of the restaurants, filling the air.

most of them owned and operated by ethnic Vietnamese.

tea shops, and food stores. Vietnamese-run travel agencies, haircutters,
accounting agencies and other businesses also can be found
there.

the capture of the capital city, then called Saigon.

the South that was backed by the American military.
The Vietnamese Embassy says up to 2
million civilians from the North and South died during
the war.
